children.subject: rip i am eecs so i must take 16b at some point. nice to hear 120 doesn't really need it though!
based on what I’ve heard it sounds like a really cool class! remember to have fun :)

An aside: im a cs major taking ee120 without ee16b. if you are not part of the batch that’s required to take 16b and you are only interested in it for the signals part, ee120 is (so far) doable without it.

history.content: EE120 is a course that feeds into other upper divs (I took it my sophomore fall and it definitely influenced my later choice of courses) so I'd be inclined to try taking it early-ish. My personal pick here is 16B. It's also supposed to help a little with 127, but I don't have personal experience with that.

because it's That Time again, I'd like to get a bit of advice on my schedule for next semester whoopee

I know I'm taking CS170, CS188, and an upper div social sciences course (tbd but that's separate from this/is for my minor) for sure; however, the unknown quantity lies in the fourth course I hope to take. I'm debating between EE127, EE16B, or CS61C here; EE127 and CS61C are more interesting to me, but EE16B is important because I do hope to ~eventually~ take EE120. also because I should probably get over with it at some point in time.

any advice is appreciated; or, if this schedule is potentially damning with all the options of the fourth class that I have presented, any other suggestions would be great!
